spec: asyncio_extra136
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-task.html#task-groups

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-task.html#task-groups — Python asyncio TaskGroup documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/taskgroups.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 259 theme — asyncio.TaskGroup class identity, MRO, and async context manager method qualnames. asyncio.TaskGroup.__name__=='TaskGroup' (len=9); asyncio.TaskGroup.__module__=='asyncio.taskgroups' (len=18); asyncio.TaskGroup.__bases__[0].__name__=='object' (len=6); asyncio.TaskGroup.__mro__.__len__()==2; asyncio.TaskGroup.__aenter__.__qualname__=='TaskGroup.__aenter__' (len=20); asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__qualname__=='TaskGroup.__aexit__' (len=19); asyncio.TaskGroup.__aenter__.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__code__.co_argcount==4 (self, et, exc, tb); asyncio.TaskGroup.__dict__.__class__.__name__=='mappingproxy'; asyncio.TaskGroup.__dict__.__len__()==15. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup was added in Python 3.11 (PEP 654). It has a flat MRO of length 2 ([TaskGroup, object]) because it has no intermediate base classes — it inherits directly from object. Its __module__ is 'asyncio.taskgroups' (len=18), NOT 'asyncio'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "asyncio.TaskGroup.__aexit__.__code__.co_argcount==4 because __aexit__ takes (self, et, exc, tb) — the three exception info parameters required by the async context manager protocol. asyncio.TaskGroup.__aenter__.__code__.co_argcount==1 because __aenter__ takes only (self). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

